tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE wind_turbine_performance_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    date DATE,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    power_output FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE WindTurbineModel (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
    rotor_diameter DECIMAL(10,2),
    hub_height DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceData (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    power_output DECIMAL(10,2),
    wind_speed DECIMAL(10,2),
    FOREIGN KEY (turbine_id) REFERENCES WindTurbineModel(id)
);

CREATE TABLE WindTurbineModels (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(50),
    manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
    blade_length INT
)

CREATE TABLE PerformanceData (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    power_output FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE EnergyOutputOptimization (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    turbine_id INT,
    optimization_date DATE,
    optimization_notes TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE performance_data (
    data_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID REFERENCES wind_turbine_models(model_id),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    wind_speed DECIMAL,
    temperature DECIMAL,
    power_output DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_records (
    record_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID REFERENCES wind_turbine_models(model_id),
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_type STRING,
    technician_name STRING
);

CREATE TABLE fault_logs (
    log_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    record_id UUID REFERENCES maintenance_records(record_id),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    fault_description TEXT,
    resolution TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE WindTurbineModel (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
model_name VARCHAR(50),
manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
rotor_diameter FLOAT,
capacity_kw INT);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceData (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
turbine_id INT,
timestamp TIMESTAMP,
wind_speed FLOAT,
energy_output FLOAT);

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceSchedule (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
turbine_id INT,
maintenance_date DATE,
maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
maintenance_details TEXT);

CREATE TABLE WeatherData (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
timestamp TIMESTAMP,
location VARCHAR(50),
temperature FLOAT,
wind_speed FLOAT);

CREATE TABLE TurbineFailureLog (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
turbine_id INT,
failure_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
failure_type VARCHAR(50),
failure_details TEXT);
